How to choose the mattress and the mattress: women and men are looking for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really imparts its quality to a good bed is the lying surface, that is, the mattress and the bedside.
First of all, they must be perfectly complemented so that they are adapted to the specific users.
During the election, numerous items come into play, including the weight, height, health and gender of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and the bedside table is placed.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend hut that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them more frequently.
If the channels of the center are not properly aerated and, above, are on a firm base, they keep moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Those who have spent a lot of time abroad often use a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
“Almost every hockey player who returned from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For their bruised shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who weather nervous system problems, so they receive poor information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem anymore, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italians Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn like after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
The viscoelastic also acts as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, e.g. single rooms, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably shrunken towards your elbows," advises the engineer Helena Prokopová, Cechu <0xC4><0x8D>aloun<0xC3><0xAD>k<0xC5><0xAF> expert at decoratér<0xC5><0xAF>, who has been specialized for many years in the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of the schools of furniture.
In the double rooms, each one needs its own bedside and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the frames at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interiors a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
“When touching it with your hand or settling on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed,” warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of bedside.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe badly and you cannot wash their sheath, which is often done today.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
Therefore, sellers give advice: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of cleaning and washing the cover, but better add a mattress protector that can be removed and washed easily.
Although mattress covers with zipper closure are currently manufactured all around their perimeter, so when they are opened they remain in two parts (something very important for the washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling in the larger models (and by one person) when lifting the mattress can seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a bedside table, do you have a firm board?
Never! Never!
As much for the beds designed to spend a night the visitors.
However, you should make (if you don’t already have them) ventilation holes in the board and you should use it with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulable sheet mattresses containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although it is always better to use a sheet mattress with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area are reinforced and their stiffness can be regulated.
Articulable sheets should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows the sheets to be pressed or even tilted in such a way that they "roll" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by the manufacturers of mattresses who, in the "males", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are cross- or tablet frames with the so-called multi-torsion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is lowered.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the right mattress and bedside, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mulky"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow should hold the head and the corners can only reach to the shoulders, so that the muscles can relax.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder pad or the softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses have something to do, it seems, with the original mattresses filled with straw.
Manufacturers continue to use more and more natural materials or at least mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are in fashion.
The petroleum-based raw materials, from which the polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh scent of forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men are "refreshed" with vegetable extracts of breeze, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel warmer.
Favorites currently?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various rigidities of cold foam and viscoelastic allows to manufacture mattresses from different areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels goes.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who play a therapeutic role usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as health care.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and mattresses.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 crowns.
The second is available free of charge.
The era of viscoelasticity with an open cell structure and high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
It initially emerged as material for NASA, because during takeoffs astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the human body, warm, exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
