The unknown winner of the new edition of the Absurdity of the Year survey was the obligation to bring to the administration documents that officials can access online.
The decision was made by more than a third of the nearly 4,000 voters.
For example, the social security administration requested an extract from the business register, although its officials can obtain it with two mouse movements.
